    "analysis": "We extracted a sample of metric rows around 04:15–04:16 +08 and observed no obvious severe spikes then: docker_004 showed modest CPU (~8%) and stable memory; os_021 showed mostly zero/low disk I/O and stable ping/memory values. Trace analysis earlier, however, found a concentrated incident at 2020-05-31 04:21:00 +08 with very large latency on docker_004 (trace.self.local.duration_p95 up to ~54.7s) and elevated error rates/latency on os_021 at the same timestamp, plus correlated row_count drops among containers. Metric samples at 04:15–04:16 did not capture the 04:21 event. To localize the root cause and reason we need metric values exactly at or immediately surrounding 04:21 for docker_004 (container-level) and os_021 (host-level) covering CPU, memory, threads, disk I/O, and network KPIs. These targeted values will help determine whether the trace spikes coincide with resource saturation (CPU/disk/network) or other causes. This is not yet resolved.",
