Review summary: Trace analysis showed a concentrated incident at 2020-05-31 04:21:00 +08:00 with very large latency spikes on docker_004 (trace.self.local.duration_p95 ≈54.7s) and correlated row_count drops. Focused metric inspection at 04:21 found a concurrent container CPU rise on docker_004 (container_cpu_used ≈50%), while host os_021 metrics did not show matching resource saturation. According to the localization rules (largest deviation wins), the evidence indicates a container-level CPU fault on docker_004 causing the observed latency and throughput drops.

